       <p>新目标英语九年级课文阅读理解试题</p>
       <p>Unit1 How do we deal with our problems?</p>
       <p>ⅠChoose the best answer according to the text.</p>
       <p>1. If people stay angry for years about a small problem what will happen?</p>
       <p>A. They may earn less money. B. Good friendships may be lost.</p>
       <p>C. They may become foolish. D. Their education may be influenced.</p>
       <p>2. Why do many students complain about school?</p>
       <p>A. Because they have too much work to do and the school rules are too strict.</p>
       <p>B. Because they feel their teachers are not kind to them.</p>
       <p>C. Because they think their classmates are hard to get along with.</p>
       <p>D. Because they are not interested in some subjects.</p>
       <p>3. As young adults, what should we try our best to do according to the passage?</p>
       <p>A. To people who can’t walk. B.To help parents do housework.</p>
       <p>C. To deal with each challenge in our education.</p>
       <p>D. What should we do if we have problems in our life?</p>
       <p>A. Worry about them. B. Face them. C. Complain about then. D. Remember them</p>
       <p>Ⅱ根据课文内容完成表格，每空不限词数。</p>
       <p>Answers. Ⅰ1-5BACDB</p>
       <p>Ⅱ1. at school 2. our families 3. forget 4. challenges 5. worse</p>
       <p>Unit2 He used to cause a lot of trouble</p>
       <p>ⅠChoose the best answer according to the text.</p>
       <p>1. How old might Martin be when his father died?</p>
       <p>A. Eleven years old. B. Fourteen years old. C. Fifteen years old. D. Sixteen years old.</p>
       <p>2.What did his mother have to do in order to pay for Martin’s education?</p>
       <p>A. She had to do housework at home. B. She had to work outside.</p>
       <p>C. She did a part-time job. D. She gave up her work.</p>
