       <p>A. what to do when we fail</p>
       <p>B. how to make requests politely</p>
       <p>C. how to get along well with others</p>
       <p>D. what to do when we meet with difficulties</p>
       <p>Ⅰ1-5BCABB</p>
       <p>Unit12 You’re supposed to write quickly!</p>
       <p>ⅠChoose the best answer according to the text.</p>
       <p>1. What is e-mail English used for?</p>
       <p>A. Saving money. B.Saving time. C. Making people happier. D. Playing games.</p>
       <p>2. What does the computer program “ICQ” mean according to the text?</p>
       <p>A. I miss you. B. I love you. C. I seek you. D. I see you.</p>
       <p>3. What might the emotion suggest in e-mail English?</p>
       <p>A. Crying. B. Smiling. C. Fighting. D. Shouting.</p>
       <p>4. Which of the following about e-mail English words is NOT true according to the text?</p>
       <p>A. BTW means “by the way”.</p>
       <p>B. CSL means “can’t stop laughing”.</p>
       <p>C. CUL8r means “see you later”. D. “gr8” is an abbreviation.</p>
       <p>5. Which of the following is NOT true according to the text?</p>
       <p>A. Using e-mail English can help you write quickly.</p>
       <p>B. There are punctuation marks in e-mail English.</p>
       <p>C. It is polite to write e-mail English at any time.</p>
       <p>D.In e-mail English, the homophone of “You are great” might be Urgr8. Ⅱ Fill in the form</p>
       <p>Ⅰ1-5 BCBDC</p>
       <p>Ⅱ1.written English 2. save time 3.abbreviation 4. homophone 5. the proper time</p>
       <p>Unit13 Receiving money makes me uncomfortable.</p>
       <p>ⅠChoose the best answer according to the text.</p>
       <p>1. What did Han Ling use to wear every time she visit her grandparents?</p>
       <p>A. A purple purse. B. An orange sweater. C. A beautiful skirt. D.</p>
       <p>A pair of new shoes.</p>
       <p>2. Where does John Wilson come from?</p>
       <p>A. China. B. The USA. C. Australia. D. Britain.</p>
       <p>3. What does John Wilson think of people who give money to others as</p>
       <p>gift?</p>
       <p>A. He thinks they are very kind. B. He thinks they are very lazy.</p>
       <p>C. He thinks they are very realistic. D. He thinks they are very busy.</p>
       <p>4. The author of the text thinks that the art of receiving is ________.</p>
       <p>A. more important than the art of giving B. much easier than the art of giving</p>
       <p>C. even harder than the art of giving D. less difficult than the art of giving</p>
       <p>5. Which of the following is NOT true according to the text?</p>
       <p>A. At the age of 12, Guo Xiaojing received a purple purse.</p>
       <p>B. To make things easier, everyone likes to just give money.</p>
       <p>C. A lot of books have been written about “the art of giving”.</p>
       <p>D. The saying “It’s the thought that counts.” Might be from England. Ⅱ Fill in the form</p>
       <p>Ⅰ1-5 BDBCB</p>
       <p>Ⅱ1.embarrassed 2. other personal things 3. happy 4. uncomfortable 5. very different thoughts</p>
       <p>Unit14 He’s already visited the place where his ancestors lived. ⅠChoose the best answer according to the text.</p>
       <p>1. Where wa Robert Qian born?</p>
       <p>A. In China. B. In Canada. C. In America. D. In Guangdong.</p>
       <p>2. What does Cathy Qin do?</p>
       <p>A. She’s an American student. B. She’s an American teacher.</p>
       <p>C. She’s an American scientist. D. She’s an American engineer.</p>
       <p>3. What language might Robert Qian speak before he came to China?</p>
       <p>A. Russian. B. Chinese. C. English. D. Japanese.</p>
       <p>4. What might Robert Qian do in his ancestors’ village?</p>
       <p>A. He drinks water from the village well. B. He goes for walks through the countryside.</p>
       <p>C. He watches the villagers do their daily activities. D. All of A,B, and C</p>
       <p>5. Which of the following is NOT true according to the text?</p>
       <p>A.Cathy Qin’s ancestors lived in China many years ago.</p>
       <p>B. Cathy Qian studied Chinese culture while she was in China..</p>
       <p>C. Robert Qian had been to China before he visited Guagndong.</p>
       <p>D. Robert Qian visited some interesting sights while he was in China. Ⅱ Fill in the form</p>
       <p>Ⅰ1-5 BACDC</p>
       <p>Ⅱ1. more about themselves 2. the local government 3. 1980 4. 2 weeks 5. young overseas Chinese 6. visit their ancestors’ village; study Chinese culture; find out more about their roots.</p>
