       <h2>范文六：<a href="/news/9C9C677C8E121D61.htm">九年级英语阅读理解大赛题</a></h2>
      </dt>
      <dd>
       <p></p>
       <p>九年级英语阅读理解大赛题</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>命题人：谢正寿</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>（一） The China’s Got Talent</p>
       <p>中国达人秀</p>
       <p>Last Sunday evening I watched the China’s Got Talent</p>
       <p>on East TV. It was wonderful, I think. Many player took part</p>
       <p>in the China’s Got Talent. The host Chen Lei was a special</p>
       <p>character person, I think. I like him very much. The program</p>
       <p>was being held in an atmosphere(气氛) of active and</p>
       <p>hot. Many audience likes his program.</p>
       <p>During the program, all audience were happy and exciting. From his column, we could find many wonderful person. There were young or old person, girls or boys, men or women. They were too fantastic. I felt it was the most happy time in my life</p>
       <p>（二）</p>
       <p>It was a very hot summer morning but inside the Pyramid it was quite cool. Tom and his classmates just walked into the Pyramid and were very surprised to see what it was like. They went to the Queen’s Room. They saw a passage ( 通道). At the end of it there was a small room. Their teacher told them that they couldn’t go into that room, because it was newly found. Tom looked towards the passage. Two of his friends Jason and Peter saw him and said “Don’t get into trouble, Tom!” when nobody was looking, Tom went up the dark passage, opened the door and walked into it. Suddenly the door closed behind him. The room was very dark, but Tom was luck that he brought a little torch (手电筒 ) with him. When he turned it on, he saw two white</p>
       <p>faces in front of him. “Oh, no!” he cried and ran to the door. He quickly opened it and went down the passage to the Queen’s Room as fast as he could. 布) off their faces and walked slowly down the passage. They couldn’t stop laughing. “That will teach him a lesson,” said Jason.</p>
       <p>根据短文意思，选择最佳答案。</p>
       <p>4. Why did Jason and Peter say “Don’t get into trouble, Tom!”?</p>
       <p>A. Because they knew that Tom was thinking of getting into that small room.</p>
       <p>B. Because Tom had got into trouble earlier that day.</p>
       <p>C. Because Tom was very much afraid.</p>
       <p>D. Because they were not good friends.</p>
       <p>5. What did Tom do when the door closed behind him?</p>
       <p>A. He was afraid and cried loudly. B. He waited quietly in the dark.</p>
       <p>C. He turned on his torch. D. He ran away quickly.</p>
       <p>6. What did Tom do when he saw two white faces?</p>
       <p>A. Nothing much. B. Go ahead.</p>
       <p>C. He wanted to see them clearly. D. Ran away quickly.</p>
       <p>7. The word “ disappeared” maybe means ______.</p>
       <p>A. found the secret B. couldn’t be seen</p>
       <p>C. cried loudly D. closed the door</p>
       <p>8. Jason and Peter laughed because ________.</p>
       <p>A. they had got Tom into trouble B. they liked telling jokes</p>
       <p>C. they had played a joke on Tom D. Tom didn’t listen to them</p>
       <p>（三）</p>
       <p>Suddenly I was woken up by a strange sound. I saw something moving near my window. I was scary and ran downstairs quickly. I found that my mum was in the kitchen, getting my brother ready for school.</p>
       <p>“Mum, did you hear anything? I, uh, I thought I saw an alien.”</p>
       <p>“Are you OK, Mike? Just a dream！” Mum answered.</p>
       <p>Then I went back to my room. As I walked to the window, I cried. I saw a little alien, no more than three feet tall, with big and black eyes. It tried to run between my legs and escape through the window. Although I was scared, for some reason, I</p>
       <p>squeezed (挤) my legs together in time to catch it. It took out something and hurt me. I felt a terrible sense of nothingness and then fell down. Then I woke up.</p>
       <p>At first, I could hardly move. I wasn’t sure whether it was a dream or not. I</p>
       <p>pulled myself out of the bed and walked downstairs. I saw my mum in the kitchen. She was really getting my brother ready for school, wearing her pink clothes. Then I realized it was just a dream because in my dream she was wearing her work clothes.</p>
       <p>From then on, I always dreamt about aliens and all the dreams felt so real. At that time, I really thought maybe I had some kind of relationship with aliens. About two months later, I stopped having such dreams. Later I realized that I used to have those dreams because I always read books or watched TV programs about aliens before I fell asleep!</p>
       <p>9. When Mike saw something moving near his window, __________.</p>
       <p>A. he was too scared to move. B. he knew it was a dream and wasn’t afraid.</p>
       <p>C. he was so scared that he fainted. D. he was scared and ran downstairs.</p>
       <p>10. Mike found that it was just a dream ___________.</p>
       <p>A. as soon as he woke up B. before he went downstairs</p>
       <p>C. when he saw his mother D. when he was hurt by the alien</p>
       <p>11. According to the passage, which of the following is true?</p>
       <p>A. Mike prepared food for his brother.</p>
       <p>B. Mike’s mother’s work clothes are pink.</p>
       <p>C. Mike’s mother was worried about his dream.</p>
       <p>D. When Mike had the dream, his family were sleeping.</p>
       <p>12. We can learn from the passage that __________.</p>
       <p>A. Mike had some kind of relationship with aliens.</p>
       <p>B. Mike got badly ill.</p>
       <p>C. Mike often read something about aliens before going to bed.</p>
       <p>D. The dreams were all about Mike’s real experiences.</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>（四）</p>
       <p>Do you drink water every day? Drinking water is good for our health. There are some scientific(科学的) ways of drinking water.</p>
       <p>It is the best medicine to drink two glasses of water in the morning. We must</p>
       <p>drink clean water and drink the water that has not been boiled. Maybe Many people think boiled water is safe and good to people’s health. In fact, it is not true. The</p>
       <p>boiling point of water is 100℃. By boiling it, most germs in water can be killed. In the past, the water was less polluted, so boiling was a good way to make clean water. But heavy metals(金属) and other dangerous things in today’s water are much more</p>
       <p>terrible than bacteria. Boiling doesn’t solve that problem. And boiling water may give us more of the dangerous things in our glass. So we must never use soft drinks to take the place of water. We must drink water in the right time. Even in winter, Water is also needed, too.</p>
       <p>Why do we must drink water in the right time? After getting up in the morning, you have less water in your body, because you weren’t drinking for the whole night. So you should drink some water to keep your health after getting up in the morning. That can prevent high blood pressure（防止高血压）, cerebral hemorrhages(脑溢血)，and so on. Drinking water at about 10 a.m. helps your body keep enough water. Drinking water at about 3 p.m. can clean out the wastes in your body. About eight o’clock in the evening is the best time to drink water. Your blood gets thicker when you sleep. Water will make your blood less thick.</p>
       <p>Besides, we should drink 2L water every day. Water is so important for our life. We should drink water often.</p>
       <p>根据短文内容，判断下列句子正（T）误（F）。</p>
       <p>13. Drinking water is the best medicine in our lives.</p>
       <p>14. We mustn’t drink no-boiled water at night.</p>
       <p>15. We should drink boiled water because there are no germs in the boiled water.</p>
       <p>16. Drinking water can clean out the wastes in our bodies.</p>
       <p>17. Every day people must drink at least 2L water.</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>B) 先阅读下面的短文，根据短文内容，然后从下列方框中选出最佳的五个句子</p>
       <p>His room is on the tenth floor, but mine is on the ninth floor. He is kind but careless, and sometimes gets into trouble.</p>
       <p>Last Friday afternoon, the young man went to a wild island to spend his holiday with his friends. They swam in the river, went fishing, played the guitar.19. _________________ Three days later, they decided to come back to the bank. Unfortunately, their boat hit a rock and soon went down. 20. _________________ With a villager’s help, all of them were out of danger. They didn’t come back until midnight. 21. _________________ So he wished to get home as soon as possible. But the lift didn’t work. He had to walk upstairs. He stopped by my door and took out a key. Of course, he could not open the door. 22. _________________ He became angry and shouted, “I’ll cut you down with a knife!”</p>
       <p>The noise woke me up and I opened the door. I understood at once what was happening and said, “You are trying to open a wrong door, Wang Yihao.”</p>
       <p>“Sorry, I can’t agree with you, Liu Feng!” he shouted, “It’s my room. You have entered it by mistake!”</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>Name: ____________________ Class:________________________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>Number:________________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>阅读比赛答题卡</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>Mark:________________________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>（一）</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>1．_______________2._______________ 3._______________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>(二)</p>
       <p>4. _____________5. _____________6. _____________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>7. _____________8. _____________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>(三)</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>9. _____________10. _____________11. _____________12. _____________</p>
       <p>（四）</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>13. _____________14. _____________15. _____________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>16. _____________17. _____________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>B）</p>
       <p>18．_____________19._____________20_____________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>21_____________22_____________</p>
       <p></p>
       <p></p>
       <p>答案:</p>
       <p>1. nine five 2. Any people 3. happy and exciting</p>
       <p>4-8．ACDBC</p>
       <p>9-12．DCBC</p>
       <p>13-17．TFFTF</p>
       <p>18-22．DFCAE九年级英语阅读理解大赛题</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>命题人：谢正寿</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>（一） The China’s Got Talent</p>
       <p>中国达人秀</p>
       <p>Last Sunday evening I watched the China’s Got Talent</p>
       <p>on East TV. It was wonderful, I think. Many player took part</p>
       <p>in the China’s Got Talent. The host Chen Lei was a special</p>
       <p>character person, I think. I like him very much. The program</p>
       <p>was being held in an atmosphere(气氛) of active and</p>
       <p>hot. Many audience likes his program.</p>
       <p>During the program, all audience were happy and exciting. From his column, we could find many wonderful person. There were young or old person, girls or boys, men or women. They were too fantastic. I felt it was the most happy time in my life</p>
       <p>（二）</p>
       <p>It was a very hot summer morning but inside the Pyramid it was quite cool. Tom and his classmates just walked into the Pyramid and were very surprised to see what it was like. They went to the Queen’s Room. They saw a passage ( 通道). At the end of it there was a small room. Their teacher told them that they couldn’t go into that room, because it was newly found. Tom looked towards the passage. Two of his friends Jason and Peter saw him and said “Don’t get into trouble, Tom!” when nobody was looking, Tom went up the dark passage, opened the door and walked into it. Suddenly the door closed behind him. The room was very dark, but Tom was luck that he brought a little torch (手电筒 ) with him. When he turned it on, he saw two white</p>
       <p>faces in front of him. “Oh, no!” he cried and ran to the door. He quickly opened it and went down the passage to the Queen’s Room as fast as he could. 布) off their faces and walked slowly down the passage. They couldn’t stop laughing. “That will teach him a lesson,” said Jason.</p>
       <p>根据短文意思，选择最佳答案。</p>
       <p>4. Why did Jason and Peter say “Don’t get into trouble, Tom!”?</p>
       <p>A. Because they knew that Tom was thinking of getting into that small room.</p>
       <p>B. Because Tom had got into trouble earlier that day.</p>
       <p>C. Because Tom was very much afraid.</p>
       <p>D. Because they were not good friends.</p>
       <p>5. What did Tom do when the door closed behind him?</p>
       <p>A. He was afraid and cried loudly. B. He waited quietly in the dark.</p>
       <p>C. He turned on his torch. D. He ran away quickly.</p>
       <p>6. What did Tom do when he saw two white faces?</p>
       <p>A. Nothing much. B. Go ahead.</p>
       <p>C. He wanted to see them clearly. D. Ran away quickly.</p>
       <p>7. The word “ disappeared” maybe means ______.</p>
       <p>A. found the secret B. couldn’t be seen</p>
       <p>C. cried loudly D. closed the door</p>
       <p>8. Jason and Peter laughed because ________.</p>
       <p>A. they had got Tom into trouble B. they liked telling jokes</p>
       <p>C. they had played a joke on Tom D. Tom didn’t listen to them</p>
       <p>（三）</p>
       <p>Suddenly I was woken up by a strange sound. I saw something moving near my window. I was scary and ran downstairs quickly. I found that my mum was in the kitchen, getting my brother ready for school.</p>
       <p>“Mum, did you hear anything? I, uh, I thought I saw an alien.”</p>
       <p>“Are you OK, Mike? Just a dream！” Mum answered.</p>
       <p>Then I went back to my room. As I walked to the window, I cried. I saw a little alien, no more than three feet tall, with big and black eyes. It tried to run between my legs and escape through the window. Although I was scared, for some reason, I</p>
       <p>squeezed (挤) my legs together in time to catch it. It took out something and hurt me. I felt a terrible sense of nothingness and then fell down. Then I woke up.</p>
       <p>At first, I could hardly move. I wasn’t sure whether it was a dream or not. I</p>
       <p>pulled myself out of the bed and walked downstairs. I saw my mum in the kitchen. She was really getting my brother ready for school, wearing her pink clothes. Then I realized it was just a dream because in my dream she was wearing her work clothes.</p>
       <p>From then on, I always dreamt about aliens and all the dreams felt so real. At that time, I really thought maybe I had some kind of relationship with aliens. About two months later, I stopped having such dreams. Later I realized that I used to have those dreams because I always read books or watched TV programs about aliens before I fell asleep!</p>
       <p>9. When Mike saw something moving near his window, __________.</p>
       <p>A. he was too scared to move. B. he knew it was a dream and wasn’t afraid.</p>
       <p>C. he was so scared that he fainted. D. he was scared and ran downstairs.</p>
       <p>10. Mike found that it was just a dream ___________.</p>
       <p>A. as soon as he woke up B. before he went downstairs</p>
       <p>C. when he saw his mother D. when he was hurt by the alien</p>
       <p>11. According to the passage, which of the following is true?</p>
       <p>A. Mike prepared food for his brother.</p>
       <p>B. Mike’s mother’s work clothes are pink.</p>
       <p>C. Mike’s mother was worried about his dream.</p>
       <p>D. When Mike had the dream, his family were sleeping.</p>
       <p>12. We can learn from the passage that __________.</p>
       <p>A. Mike had some kind of relationship with aliens.</p>
       <p>B. Mike got badly ill.</p>
       <p>C. Mike often read something about aliens before going to bed.</p>
       <p>D. The dreams were all about Mike’s real experiences.</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>（四）</p>
       <p>Do you drink water every day? Drinking water is good for our health. There are some scientific(科学的) ways of drinking water.</p>
       <p>It is the best medicine to drink two glasses of water in the morning. We must</p>
       <p>drink clean water and drink the water that has not been boiled. Maybe Many people think boiled water is safe and good to people’s health. In fact, it is not true. The</p>
       <p>boiling point of water is 100℃. By boiling it, most germs in water can be killed. In the past, the water was less polluted, so boiling was a good way to make clean water. But heavy metals(金属) and other dangerous things in today’s water are much more</p>
       <p>terrible than bacteria. Boiling doesn’t solve that problem. And boiling water may give us more of the dangerous things in our glass. So we must never use soft drinks to take the place of water. We must drink water in the right time. Even in winter, Water is also needed, too.</p>
       <p>Why do we must drink water in the right time? After getting up in the morning, you have less water in your body, because you weren’t drinking for the whole night. So you should drink some water to keep your health after getting up in the morning. That can prevent high blood pressure（防止高血压）, cerebral hemorrhages(脑溢血)，and so on. Drinking water at about 10 a.m. helps your body keep enough water. Drinking water at about 3 p.m. can clean out the wastes in your body. About eight o’clock in the evening is the best time to drink water. Your blood gets thicker when you sleep. Water will make your blood less thick.</p>
       <p>Besides, we should drink 2L water every day. Water is so important for our life. We should drink water often.</p>
       <p>根据短文内容，判断下列句子正（T）误（F）。</p>
       <p>13. Drinking water is the best medicine in our lives.</p>
       <p>14. We mustn’t drink no-boiled water at night.</p>
       <p>15. We should drink boiled water because there are no germs in the boiled water.</p>
       <p>16. Drinking water can clean out the wastes in our bodies.</p>
       <p>17. Every day people must drink at least 2L water.</p>
       <p></p>
       <p>B) 先阅读下面的短文，根据短文内容，然后从下列方框中选出最佳的五个句子</p>
       <p>His room is on the tenth floor, but mine is on the ninth floor. He is kind but careless, and sometimes gets into trouble.</p>
       <p>Last Friday afternoon, the young man went to a wild island to spend his holiday with his friends. They swam in the river, went fishing, played the guitar.19. _________________ Three days later, they decided to come back to the bank. Unfortunately, their boat hit a rock and soon went down. 20. _________________ With a villager’s help, all of them were out of danger. They didn’t come back until midnight. 21. _________________ So he wished to get home as soon as possible. But the lift didn’t work. He had to walk upstairs. He stopped by my door and took out a key. Of course, he could not open the door. 22. _________________ He became angry and shouted, “I’ll cut you down with a knife!”</p>
       <p>The noise woke me up and I opened the door. I understood at once what was happening and said, “You are trying to open a wrong door, Wang Yihao.”</p>
       <p>“Sorry, I can’t agree with you, Liu Feng!” he shouted, “It’s my room. You have entered it by mistake!”</p>
       <p></p>
